        "text": "1 Thessalonians 5:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The members of the church are by turns to greet one another (not each other in Peter’s name) with the kiss of charity, thus testifying to their brotherly love for each other (see Meyer on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 16:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Instead of the Pauline: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐν ἁγίῳ φιλ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., there is here: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐν φιλ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀγάπης",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
