        "text": ",” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the kiss, which is the type and expression of Christian brotherly love.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The final benediction is likewise similar to those in the epistles of Paul; only that in these ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "χάρις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " stands in the place of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰρήνη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ephesians 6:23-24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", both occur; cf. too, 3 John 15). By the addition of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τοῖς ἐν Χρ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πάντες",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " are designated according to their nature as such, who live in union with Christ, and to whom, therefore, the benediction here pronounced belongs.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
